# Portfolio Code Conventions

## Structure
- App Router: `src/app/` (layout, page, globals.css)
- Sections: `src/components/sections/` — one component per scroll section
- Shared UI: `src/components/`
- All static content: `src/utils/data.ts` (typed exports, `satisfies`)
- GSAP client import: `@/lib/gsap-client` (not raw `gsap` in components)

## Components
- Sections with GSAP or hooks: `"use client"` at top
- Footer without interactivity: server component OK
- Language: `useLanguage()` from `@/context/TextContext`
- Localized strings: `Record<Language, T>` or `LocalizedText` from `data.ts`

## Styling
- Tailwind only — match existing palette (sky/slate)
- Responsive: mobile-first, `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints like existing sections
- Keep animation subtle; respect reduced motion patterns if adding new motion

## Data changes
- Add new section content to `data.ts` first, then wire component
- New navbar item: update `hero[language].navbar` + section `id`
- Project detail anchor: `refMore: "#slug"` matches `id={detail.logo}` in Details

## Don't
- Move content into components as hardcoded strings — keep `data.ts` as single source
- Swap tutorial-project framing into case studies without user confirmation
- Large refactors when user asked for one task ID from the plan
